race.comment: SAVOCA (9) is capable on his day and will find this more to his liking. Chipped away late when third over 1200m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Will relish the good tempo back to the 1100m and will be doing his best work late. DEBUSSY (3) slow into stride and warmed up when the race was all over with a handy sixth over 1205m at Coffs Harbour in the Pink Silks BM82 over 1205m. Back in grade and sure to be thereabouts. HEIR APPARENT (1) failed to match it with them early and got further back than expected when a poor last over 1205m at Coffs Harbour in the Pink Silks over 1205m. Well placed back to this trip with the claim. PRATT (4) total forgive from the wide gate first-up with a tiring ninth over 1000m at Gosford in a BM64. Proven second-up and since fitted with a 1000m trial win. Blinkers go on and must be kept safe.
